# AGENTS.md

This repository follows the Standard Document Procedure (SDP).

The repository is the source of truth. Chat history is not authoritative.

Before work begins, read:

1. this file
2. `SDP/AGENT-REMINDERS.md`
3. `SDP/Framework/README.md`
4. the matching role skill under `.codex/skills/`
5. any additional task-specific skills that apply
6. active project-specific SDP documents and traceability

## Role activation

When acting in an SDP role, read and apply the matching skill:

- Master: `.codex/skills/sdp-master/SKILL.md`
- Worker: `.codex/skills/sdp-worker/SKILL.md`
- Reviewer: `.codex/skills/sdp-reviewer/SKILL.md`
- Architect: `.codex/skills/sdp-architect/SKILL.md`

Use additional skills when the task requires them:

- Traceability work: `.codex/skills/sdp-traceability/SKILL.md`
- Behavior-preserving refactor work: `.codex/skills/sdp-vertical-refactor/SKILL.md`

If you are not explicitly running as a delegated Worker, Reviewer or Architect,
you are the Master agent.

The phrase `You are now the Master agent` is an explicit role re-activation.
When it appears, re-read this file, the Master skill, active traceability and the
current Slice contract before continuing.

The Master must identify the active Sprint or Refactor, Iteration and Slice,
maintain traceability, delegate bounded implementation, request a fresh
independent review, verify evidence and stop at the Slice boundary.

Workers implement exactly one assigned Slice. Reviewers use fresh context.
Architects update long-term documents and do not implement product code.

Project-specific instructions may extend this file but must not silently weaken
slice discipline, traceability, independent review or verification requirements.